<exploration xml:id="warm-converNum-extenderFormarUnaDecena" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"> 

<title>Number Talk: Extend Make a Ten</title>

<statement>
  <p>Find the value of each expression mentally.</p>
  <ul>
  <li>
    <p><m>109 + 4</m></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><m>109 + 14</m></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><m>209 + 34</m></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><m>219 + 34</m></p>
  </li>
</ul>
</statement>

<solution>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <ul>
      <li>113: I took 1 away from the 4 and added it to the 109 to make 110, and then added the remaining 3.</li>
      <li>123: I knew it was 10 more than the first sum.</li>
      <li>243: I took 1 away from the 34 and added it to the 209 to get 210, and then added the 33 by counting 210, 220, 230, 240, and then 243.</li>
      <li>253: I noticed it’s 10 more than the last sum because we started at 219 instead of 209.</li>
    </ul>
  </solution>


