  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="narrative-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <p>The purpose of this Number Talk is to elicit strategies students have for adding two numbers when one number is close to a whole number of tens. These understandings help students develop fluency in addition. Students may look for and make use of structure (MP7) in a number of ways. For example, they may add 1 to the first addend to make a full ten and subtract 1 from the second addend to find each sum. They may also notice how the addends compare to those in the previous expression and use the change to find the new sum.</p>
<p>In this string, students may also add the tens and ones separately to find the sum. Adding by place value is the focus of upcoming work. This Number Talk also enables the teacher to learn the strategies students currently have for addition.</p>
  </paragraphs>

